Just a repost from @spongebob I thought was an a amazing read on the zodiac sign.
.
.
Want to congratulate everyone on Gemini Venus retrograde finally being over! The shadow period is complete, and everyone will be moving forward with their relationships. It’s also such a nice time for some cuffing from now till September, as long you’re social distancing and finding trust with people you choose to get close with. 
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
my ONLY red flag is that I’m a LEO.
.
.
Today, on July 12th: Venus has an encounter with the love of her life, Mars. Both of them in Leo, the sign that is all about honoring soul truth. Venus is the planet of beauty, relationships, romance, and the arts. Mars is the planet that dictates our passion, anger, drive, and how we take action. As the myths go: Venus was in a loveless marriage to Vulcan, they both had countless affairs outside the marriage. No one seemed to care, till Helios told Vulcan of Venus' affair to Mars. Humiliated by the news, Vulcan swore to humiliate Venus and Mars. Vulcan made an invisible net around Venus' bed to trap whoever rested on it. One night Venus invited Mars over to rest, and they both got tangled by the net. Seeing that his trap was successful, Vulcan kept the pair strung up and invited the Olympians over to expose their affair and further humiliate them. Venus did not end up divorcing Vulcan. Mars ended up marrying a forgettable deity. The romantic in me is sad to know they did not ultimately end up together, for the politics of the heavens could not allow it. However through the movements of their heavenly bodies we can follow their continuous affair. For eons, Mars and Venus have managed to ignite their love and meet each other at least once every two years.  Today, is one of those rare meetings Venus has with Mars, they won’t see each other till February 2022. Listen to your heart and honor your truth. A new 2 year cycle has begun with with your passion/drive/values, and since both sign are in Leo there’s a positive structure to celebrarte yourself and everything that makes you feel seen.
.
.
.

#aries #taurus #gemini #leo #virgo #libra #scorpio #sagittarius #aquarius #capricorn #pisces #astrology #zodiac #horoscope #zodiacfacts #zodiacposts #astrologymemes

node.text:
I am the astro shorty that leaves when the energy calls for it.
.
.
Mercury is finally moving into Cancer on July 11th signaling the end of its Retrograde/Eclipse/Gemini journey.  Mercury has been in Gemini since May 3rd, and during that time secrets and information you needed to know got revealed to you. Mercury is the planet that allows us to formulate, analyze, and make sense of the world around us. And when Mercury is in Gemini they love to gossip, spread information, give you another opinion/option, and a whimsical push into a new direction. Then on July 9th, 9:17 pm (est), we have a new moon in cancer. A energetic reminder to allow more warmth into your life. A reminder to keep yourself nourished. To do what keeps you safe. And to take out things in your life that doesn’t makes you feel safe, warm, or nourished.  With these two cosmic event, this weekend will be a shift in the universe. Keep close attention! Take in any information and secrets that are coming out, because once Mercury goes into Cancer things will be quiet for a bit. Maybe that’s needed after these gossipy last 2 months. And most importantly it’s also the weekend to keep your house in order and water the plants your growing. I love water full/new moon. And if you can find degradable paper, write down things you want to let go in that piece of paper and flush it down the toilet or throw it into a body of water. It’s time to nourish yourself! Manifest a bigger and better home for yourself. 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
I’m just thinking about them (Saturn) 🪐. 
.
.
.
Saturn is the planet of Karma, Rules, Authority, and Boundaries. The Great Teacher. Saturn typically shows where we got a lack out of life or had too much of when we were young. It is the planet that my teacher Anne always tells you to look at. It is where we go to build meaning in our lives. Saturn is where we look at to see what we need in order to build structures in our life. We need to have structure in order to have a proper foundation to be our fullest self. And as I said in my previous post, whenever we go through a Saturn transit:  we are asked to build and rethink about the structures of our lives. We think more harshly on what keeps us going and if we are doing the work to get where we want to go in life. Saturn isn’t always harsh, however, if you’ve done the work. Saturn likes to reward people. And although I’m not really going to go in depth about it, I did do it on my podcast (@planetdirtbag). Where I talked with @lisastardustastro author of “Saturn Return Survival Guide” all about it. Please check it out wherever podcasts are found.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#aries #taurus #gemini #leo #virgo #libra #scorpio #sagittarius #aquarius #capricorn #pisces #astrology #zodiac #horoscope #zodiacfacts #zodiacposts #astrologymemes

node.text:
what’s wrong with people? Can’t even change their own birth chart for the ones they love.
.
I would have made sure our Venus is in each other’s 7th house, and our moon/Venus is making positive aspect to each other. But, in all seriousness. After taking @annabelgat Astrology class centered around Love. There is a lesson I had to be reminded about. A chart has so much dimensions and layers to it , even in compatibility, the way one chart can manifest in so many different ways. No one is really doomed in romance, and people can still be compatible even with harsh aspects going against one another. The most important lesson is romance, is to keep putting in effort. 
.
In other news, on July 1st: Mars is in opposition of Saturn. Mars is how we take action, our drive, our passion. Saturn is our boundaries, our structure, karma. Saturn likes to halt and stop anything it comes in contact with, to keep people in check and to remind people to tie their shoelaces. Actions are put to a halt. You’ll have to consider if the actions your doing right now is aligned with the things you want to build your life on. If you are doing the right things to get your life going. It’s a transit that tries to make sure you’re taking care of yourself. A transit that reminds you to stop and think if you’re taking action that is building towards your future. Mars is in Cancer, Saturn is in Capricorn. Expect things to be a little melancholy and maybe a bit sad. Our energy will be low. So keep hydrated. If you’re feeling down; I suggest to journal about where you are and where you want to go.
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Toxic traits the signs are into.
.
Use: Sun, Moon, Venus. 
.
June 20th, Jupiter goes retrograde. Jupiter is the planet of expansion, abundance, luck, justice, and philosophy. It’s the energy we tap into to expand our soul, expand our mind, expand our beliefs, and expand what it means to be us. It goes retrograde for about 4 months every year. And while it is in Pisces right now, it will retrograde back into Aquarius. Jupiter going retrograde is the time of the year when we stop to think about how we want to grow, what makes us feel fulfilled, and how we can give/get more out of the universe. So, think back to late March (2021): your social groups/dreams/ideals because you will be revisiting that chapter of your life as Jupiter revisit’s that time of our lives. It’s a great time to connect with friends and social groups you had a falling or lost touch with. To expand your social circle. To embrace new communities. And to allow yourself to be social and learn from the world. It’s party time.
.
.
.
Brining this back because Gemini season is almost over. The sun is going over my Gemini Venus/Rising, and triggering every other mutable placement in my chart. Doesn’t help that Mercury retrograde has woken-up every area of my life over the past month, and the Eclipse accelerated the manifestation of many beautiful things to sprout into my life. In short: I been really going through it. In a positive way! Been too busy to be online. Only way I’m informed of what’s going on in the global world is by the various oddities I befriended over the past month. Been networking with vampires, working for witches, talking to sirens, communicating with extra dimension beings through my pod @planetdirtbag . And will be back online soon enough! 
.
.
.

node.text:
I just want to hear how sexy and cool, I am.
.
Eclipse! Eclipse! Eclipse! Time has been speeding up more than usual. The sun/moon isn’t working at its optimal level. Fated moments, supernatural creatures, and vortexes all around. Thankfully the last eclipse of the summer has occurred and time should go back to normal by June 24th. The Upcoming full moon will be one where we can go back to manifesting. Mercury ends it’s retrograde on the 22nd. All I can say as we are gearing towards the sunrise of a long night of the souls. To keep vigilant. To stay aware. All is getting revealed at this time. And peoples are showing their true faces. The universe is showing its full force.
.
.
.
Been less active than usual. Prob, for the best? Taking an astrology course, learning and doing more witchcraft, working for a nyc council-man campaign, getting deeper into Kabbalah, trying to not get my energy stolen by the vampires of the nyc scene, and writing astrology. 
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
How’s I been handling with all the Cosmic Energy in the air. Eclipse season, speeding up our emotional consciousness. Mercury Retrograde: delaying everything and miscommunication everywhere that needs a reevaluation. And today Mars is opposite Pluto (June 5th). It’s a major moment to take action against power structure. Mars is our will, our energy, passion, and how we exert ourselves. Pluto deals with power dynamics, survival, and is energy beyond the self. In Kabbalah it’s associated with Da ath (which Im currently obsessed with learning about). Pluto is associated with death and transformation, and it brings about a lessons in life that can only be learned through absence or death. It is knowledge we push back from learning, it is energy we don’t really know to handle, but when it comes we learn a lot about our innate truth. Mars is opposite Pluto, we are moving. Actions are being taken against powers and energy that test our place in the universe. We are fighting with energies that tests our power, in order to gain a better conscious realization of our drive and actions. Although with an opposition the energy is heated. Be careful, stay aware, and try not to get into any fights. People are emotional. People really want to fight. The world is shifting, and I will be drinking some coffee and smoking to handle this. Although I do love moments and crisis in life that shows me who I am. Wishing everyone lots of luck!
.
.
.
.

node.text:
im allowed to blame Mercury retrograde now.
.
.
.
It’s that time of the year when I can blame my poor life choices on Mercury going Gatorade.
.

Yesterday (May-29) Mercury began its retrograde phase. However the beginning of the Mercury retrograde’ began with its shadow period (May 14th). Whatever conversations and themes that went on from May 14th till May 29th will be repeated, now Mercury goes retrograde till the 22nd. So pay attention to the conversations and themes that went on in your life. You’ll have a chance to fix and revisit those conversations again.  I know you may be asking: “What is a Mercury Retrograde”? Well, it’s a period of 3-5 weeks in which the planet Mercury appears to rotate backwards. The planet of Mercury deals with technology, thoughts, communication, cognition, and travel. Ghost of your past coming back? Perfectly functioning car breaking down? Trip getting canceled? iPhone starts slowing down? Sounds like Mercury Retrograde. Mercury does this in order for you to be conscious, be ready for anything, get your shit together, and re-examine yourself. It wants you to improve your communication. And wants you to be more cognitive of your surroundings. Be more analytical of your world. Mercury wants you to be on top of this reality and make good choices. Since Mercury will be in Gemini, we will be asked to look at the duality of life, to ask questions, to be inquisitive, and gain a better understanding of our words and our thought processes. Also, after Mercury retrograde ends on June, 22nd. You will have to repeat the themes and conversations that were going on just one more time, the 3rd time, till July 7th. However the 3rd phase, the Post Mercury retrograde is always more cognitive and very level headed. The whole Mercury retrograde experience is a great time to make amends, rework your life, and fix past problems. It’s a fun time, I think. And Gemini loves to do things twice, and get new information. It will be a busy, busy, period.

.
.
.

node.text: Just wanted to remind everyone we are in Eclipse season. You can definitely learn more about it in my highlight! It started back on the 11th of May, the season will continue till June 24th. Eclipse seasons are time of massive energetic shifts. In ancient times it was thought to signal the end of the world. It’s true in a sense. It’s signals massive endings, but also beginnings. Life is more energetically charged, fated events flourishing all around. It’s one of those periods where you really can’t anticipate what’s going to happen next, the energy is just so potent. Time moves quickly. Doors will be closing and opening all around you. Emotions are more intense. Revelations being spilled all around. Changes in power dynamics. I just hope everyone can stay vigilant and use their energy to help others. This Eclipse season is quite a hurricane. #astrology #BloodMoon
